result.execSummary:
The defendant Nathan George Keuten was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
9:52 AM Defendant Nathan George Keuten in court, in custody.  Attorney Michael Charles Hoffman in court for Nathan George Keuten.  Attorney Chad C La Lor in court for State of Wisconsin. State recites agreement that repeaters in each count struck. For count 1, 29 days jail with credit for 22 days -time served, concurrent with Count 2 and pay a $150 fine plus costs. For Count 2, 29 days jail with credit for 22 days - time served, concurrent with Count 1. Defendant pleads no contest. Attorney Hoffman stipulates to a factual basis. Court accepts the Defendant's plea and finds that the Defendant's plea has been freely, voluntarily and intelligently made. The Defendant understands all the rights he is waiving by his plea. The Defendant is found guilty and Judgment of Conviction is entered.

Court strikes repeaters in each count and imposes for count 1, 29 days jail with credit for 22 days-time served and pay a $150 fine plus costs. For Count 2, 29 days jail with credit for 22 days - time served, concurrent with Count 1.
